<p class="courseblockdesc">
Planning and analyzing surveys. Topics include simple random sampling, stratified sampling, systematic sampling, ratio estimation, and cluster sampling. Case studies with applications to real situations. Course Information: 3 undergraduate hours. 4 graduate hours. Prerequisite(s): <a href="/search/?P=IDS%20371" title="IDS&#160;371" class="bubblelink code" onclick="return showCourse(this, 'IDS 371');">IDS&#160;371</a>.<br />
